                            <comment id="15823396" author="varunthacker" created="Mon, 16 Jan 2017 03:13:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For example , here is a screenshot of what happens when we click on one of them&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15828785" author="ctargett" created="Wed, 18 Jan 2017 21:17:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The issue here is that the page in the UI pulls from the MBeanRequestHandler, which has not yet been updated to return the data from the new metrics.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Besides updating the MBean handler, another possible solution would be to modify the UI to not show those categories until it is updated.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15829100" author="tomasflobbe" created="Thu, 19 Jan 2017 01:09:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Don&apos;t know much about the UI code, but this patch excludes the plugin types that have no stats&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15838537" author="tomasflobbe" created="Wed, 25 Jan 2017 20:41:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=upayavira&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;upayavira&quot;&gt;upayavira&lt;/a&gt; any thoughts? Maybe we can get this in 6.4.1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15838566" author="upayavira" created="Wed, 25 Jan 2017 20:57:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tflobbe&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tflobbe&quot;&gt;tflobbe&lt;/a&gt; one of the points of doing the conversion was to make the code more accessible to non-JS developers. I&apos;m afraid I&apos;m not doing Solr dev at the moment, but your patch looks simple - does it work?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15838632" author="tomasflobbe" created="Wed, 25 Jan 2017 21:41:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I saw your comment on some other Jira and thought you were back &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;. It does work, it just skips the empty stats&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
